    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="nar.03332.001.jpg" type="verso"/>
           
            <ab>Sept. 11, 1871.</ab>
            <ab>Hon. J. A. J. Creswell,</ab>
            <ab>Postmaster General.</ab>
            <ab>Sir:</ab>
            <ab>Referring to my letter to you under date of the 24th ult. relative to the escape from jail of the mail-robber Gilmore, I now have the honor to enclose a copy of a letter addressed to this Department, under date of the 8th instant
            <note type="authorial" place="left" rend="none">mail robber Gilmore</note>
            
            <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="nar.03332.002.jpg" type="recto"/>
            
            by the Marshal of the United States for the Western District of Missouri upon this subject.</ab>
            <ab>Very respectfully, &amp;c</ab>
            <ab>A. T. Akerman,</ab>
            <ab>Attorney General.</ab>
            <note type="authorial" place="left" rend="none">see pp. 209 219 ante</note>
            
        </body>
    </text>
